---  
description: Use when creating component variants in code and corresponding Headless Variant Definition items in Sitecore.  
globs: ["src/components/**/*.ts", "src/components/**/*.tsx", ".sitecore/component-map.ts"]  
alwaysApply: false  
---  
  
Use variants when the same datasource and fields support multiple visual layouts.  
  
Code rules:  
- Keep variants in the same component file  
- Export `Default` first  
- Use PascalCase export names like `Default`, `Compact`, `WithImage`  
  
Sitecore rules:  
- Create variant items under:  
  `/sitecore/content/<site-collection>/<site-name>/Presentation/Headless Variants/`  
- Create a container for the component  
- Create Variant Definition items inside it  
- Variant Definition item names must exactly match the code export names  
  
Examples:  
- Code export: `Compact`  
- Variant item name: `Compact`  
  
If the variant dropdown is missing:  
- Check the Headless Variants items  
- Check the casing of the variant names  
- Ensure `Default` exists  